OL,7,FIn a statement, the Welsh Government
OL,8,Fsaid: "We are grateful to the
OL,9,FCommittee for their work and will
OL,10,Fconsider the report carefully. We
OL,11,Fcontinue to work closely with the UK
OL,12,FGovernment and others to ensure EU
OL,13,Fcitizens who wish to remain in Wales
OL,14,Fcan do so and access their rights
OL,15,Funder the Withdrawal Agreement.
OL,17,F"This year we have allocated #140,000
OL,18,Fto continue EU Citizens Advice
OL,19,FServices, supporting those who need
OL,20,Fhelp with applications and accessing
OL,21,Fpublic services."
